						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachakkaravartti Kulōttuṅgachōḷa I Year 50, <hi rend="italic">Āḍi</hi> 3, <hi rend="italic">Saturday, Pañchami Sadayam</hi> = June 28, 1119 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Built in. Seems to record that Vāgai-uḍaiyān Kāri Karumāṇikkam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājarāja ulagavēḷāṉ sold a piece of land to the temple (Ādichaṇḍēśvaradēvar) after the receipt of price. Also mentions Nelmali-nāḍu (a sub-division) of Rājēndrachōḻa-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

